link:labelLink.link:label: Superannuation
Superannuation Account Details Account Activity Status Code
This indicates the activity status of the superannuation account.

Valid values are: Active = Active Open And Not Lost = Open and not lost Open And Lost = Open and lost Closed = Closed Lost Inactive = Lost - Inactive Lost Uncontactable = Lost - Uncontactable Not Lost = The member is neither uncontactable nor inactive Uncontactable = The member has had no contact within the past 12 months Inactive = The member's account is inactive and has not received a contribution or rollover for the member within the past five years
Superannuation Account Details Account Contributions Code
A code which indicates the types of contributions that can be accepted by a superannuation account.

Valid values are: All = All types of contributions are accepted. None = Contributions are not accepted. Non-government = All types of contributions are accepted other than those from the government. Government only = Only government contributions are accepted.
Superannuation Account Details Account Phase Code
A code which indicates the phase of a superannuation account.

Valid values are: Accumulation = The account is in accumulation phase and will accept payments, rollovers and contributions. Retirement = The account is in retirement phase and funds are accessible. Insurance Only = The account has been established for insurance purposes only, not to fund retirement. Closed = The account has been closed and the member no longer has an interest in the fund.
Superannuation Account Details Defined Benefit Interest Indicator
This indicates whether the superannuation account has a defined benefit interest.
A choice of TRUE/FALSE values. true = The superannuation account has a defined benefit interest. false = The superannuation account does not have a defined benefit interest.
Superannuation Account Details Government Rollover Indicator
This indicates whether the superannuation account accepts government rollover.
A choice of TRUE/FALSE values. true = The superannuation account accepts government rollover. false = The superannuation account does not accept government rollover.
Superannuation Account Details Grandfathering Indicator
This indicates whether grandfathering provisions apply to the superannuation account for superannuation contributions.

A choice of TRUE/FALSE values. true = Grandfathering provisions apply to the superannuation account for superannuation contributions. false = Grandfathering provisions do not apply to the superannuation account for superannuation contributions.
Superannuation Account Details Income Stream Account Status Code
A code which indicates the income stream account status that applies to the member's superannuation account.

Valid values are: Open = The member's account is open. Transition to retirement income stream (TRIS) = The member's account is a transition to retirement income stream. Non capped defined benefit income stream (non-TRIS) = The member's account is not a capped defined benefit income stream and not a TRIS. Non capped defined benefit income stream (TRIS) = The member's account is not a capped defined benefit income stream and is a TRIS. Capped defined benefit income stream (1 July 2017 onwards) = The member's account is a capped defined benefit income stream that commenced post 1 July 2017. Capped defined benefit income stream (pre 1 July 2017) = The member's account is a capped defined benefit income stream that existed pre 1 July 2017. Market linked capped defined benefit income stream (pre 1 July 2017) = The member's account is a market linked capped defined benefit income stream that existed pre 1 July 2017. Closed = The member's account is closed.
Superannuation Account Details Innovative Income Stream Product Indicator
This indicates whether the superannuation account has an innovative income stream product.
A choice of TRUE/FALSE values. true = The superannuation account has an innovative income stream product. false = The superannuation account does not have an innovative income stream product.
Superannuation Account Details Outward Rollover Indicator
This indicates whether the superannuation account accepts outward rollover.
A choice of TRUE/FALSE values. true = The superannuation account accepts outward rollover. false = The superannuation account does not accept outward rollover.
Superannuation Member Details Deferred Tax Debt Account Status Code
A code which indicates the deferred tax debt account status for the superannuation member.

Valid values are: Exists = The superannuation member has an existing deferred tax debt account. None = The superannuation member does not have a deferred tax debt account. Unconfirmed = Deferred debt account status has not been confirmed for superannuation member.
